                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1272</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-28T23:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1917—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 27, 7 p.m. As Cuban forces occupied Guantanamo and its port of
                    Caimanero yesterday, it is assumed that Government officers have been
                    established in offices and rebels desiring have surrendered. The port is open.
                    The President is sending ship with supplies for poor people of Guantanamo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
